  "wikitext": "\n'''1-2-090\n\nUnit of linear measure chiefly used at sea. It is approximately one minute of latitude.\n\nThe international nautical mile is 1852 m (or 6076 feet) (International agreement at the I.H.B. Conference of 1929).\n\n\nReference: I.H.B.\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Nautical mile}}\n[[Category:1.2 Navigation]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]"
